The search for a Durban hiker by rescue teams came to an end,   following four days of intensive searching at Monks Cowl in Drakensberg. The 57 year old hiker was last seen on Sunday, 15 March. Jonathan Mackenzie was found this morning (Friday, 20 March) by local hikers in the Drakensberg area, in a good condition. Meanwhile, the search for a second person that was reported missing in Emtsheni, Bergville, is underway. Rescue teams commenced with the search early this morning. This is a developing story and updates will follow as events unfold.